(587, 588, '0x0100003100005E11', 'YARD / CUNOESSE', 'Talk to Cunoesse to find out she\'s a girl.\n\n\"I have nothing interesting say, talk to Cuno!\"\n\nOr approach her from the backyard to catch her off-guard and have something-resembling an actual dialogue with her.', '396', '6'),
(588, 589, '0x0100003100006766', 'Replace lost boule', 'Due to some confusion over the game René and Gaston are playing, you threw one of their pétanque *boules* far in the sea. The shot was excellent, but now you owe them a *boule*... or at least similar-looking metal sphere.', '0', '0'),
(589, 590, '0x0100003100006790', 'Make truce with Cuno', 'You tried to punch Cuno and failed catastrophically. Now you need to make a truce with him to gain access to his knowledge. Offer him something he might like. Smokes? A \"Man from Hjelmdall\" book?', '0', '0'),
(590, 591, '0x010000310000679B', 'Find your other shoe', 'Seems like your green snakeskin shoe is missing its partner. You should find it before you go venturing into the wild unknown. Two shoes are better than one -- unite them again.', '0', '0'),
(591, 592, '0x01000031000067A3', 'Interview cafeteria manager', 'The cafeteria manager of the Whirling-in-Rags might know something about the murder that happened in the yard. Ask him about it.', '0', '0'),
(592, 593, '0x01000031000067AB', 'Inspect victim\'s body', 'Inspect the body hanging in the back yard of the Whirling-in-Rags. This is a preliminary inspection, you just need to suppress the urge to throw up and approach it.', '0', '0'),
(593, 594, '0x01000031000067B3', 'Report your badge missing', 'You need to report your missing badge to the 41st Precinct as soon as possible. The lieutenant said that you can use the radio in his motorcar to call your station.', '0', '0'),
(594, 595, '0x01000031000067C3', 'Find money for rent and pay Garte', 'You need to find 20 reál to pay for your room at the Whirling, or it will be locked after 21.00. As long as you don\'t have a free place to stay you have to do this every night.', '0', '0'),
(595, 596, '0x01000031000067CB', 'Pay for damages', 'You need to pay for the damages you caused in the Whirling-in-Rags, or you won\'t have a place to stay tonight. Ask around for money and be careful with your spending. If you\'re unsure how much you owe, ask Garte.', '0', '0'),
(596, 597, '0x01000031000067D3', 'Find smokes and smoke them', 'You need to get your hands on some cigarettes and then smoke them... for those massive bonuses. Find a pack, put it in your hand (equip it in the HELD slot in your INVENTORY), and the smokes will do the rest.', '0', '0'),
(597, 598, '0x0100003100006E87', 'Talk to Garte for Sylvie', 'Sylvie asked you to talk to Garte and tell him she\'s sorry. Go to the cafeteria manager and relay the news, maybe it will help you somehow?', '0', '0'),
(598, 599, '0x01000031000073ED', 'Talk to Joyce about the pale without Kim', 'Lieutenant Kitsuragi does not want you to hear about something called the *pale*, probably thinking it will prove traumatic. Return to Joyce once he is not there, and ask her about it. *Or* get him to step away for a second.', '0', '0'),
(599, 600, '0x010000310000A28E', 'Track down your badge', 'It\'s unclear how you should go about finding a tiny piece of plastic in a world as huge as this. Maybe you\'ll just *stumble* across it, down the line? Miracles happen.', '0', '0'),
(600, 601, '0x010000310000A2A8', 'KINEEMA ORB / torque talk', 'Kim has a sweet ride, the Coupris Kineema - the sports version of the Coupris 40 police motor-carriage. You should definitely talk about it.', '395', '0'),
(601, 602, '0x010000310000AB30', 'KINEEMA / SYLVIE', 'Your wildly successful phone call to Sylvie Malaiika.', '396', '67'),
(602, 603, '0x010000310000B46B', 'YARD / CUNO', '* All greeting except \"Making amends\".\n* Throwing up advice.\n* Buy pants.', '396', '5'),
(603, 604, '0x010000310000C8AB', 'YARD / PILE OF ETERNITE', 'Someone has left some crumbly looking eternite panels leaning against this wall. Most suspicious.', '396', '348'),
(604, 605, '0x010000310000C90B', 'CONTAINERYARD / EVRART', 'Evrart Claire is the head of the Dockworkers\' Union. Wealthy, lazy, smart cat - player.\n\nIn this dialogue you can:\n\n* Enlist Evrart\'s aid to get the body down (he asks measurehead to do it).\n* Get bent and earn a daily income by doing so (corrupt cop).\n* Find out about the neighbourhood.', '376', '396'),
(605, 606, '0x010000310000C912', 'EVRART ORB / nighttime desk', 'The desk has been cleaned out for the night.', '0', '0'),
(606, 607, '0x010000310000C919', 'CONTAINERYARD / EASY-LEO', 'A simpleton dockyard-worker. Only person besides Evrart and Mega-Rich left in the container yard. He\'s making a banner.', '79', '0'),
(607, 608, '0x010000320000004D', 'PLAZA ORB / stone spheres', 'Enormous *boules* worthy of a real man.', '0', '0'),
(608, 609, '0x0100003200000070', 'PLAZA ORB / doomed cellar y', 'There is something down there...', '0', '0'),
(609, 610, '0x01000032000000CF', 'PLAZA ORB / sea hearing', 'You hear the distant squall of seabirds.', '0', '0'),
(610, 611, '0x010000320000019B', 'APT / EMPTY ROOM DOOR', 'APARTMENT #10. A door leading to the apt with a real estate agent.', '0', '0'),
(611, 612, '0x01000032000001A2', 'APT / BATHROOM DOOR', '', '0', '0'),
(612, 613, '0x0100003400003F75', 'PLAZA ORB / erotica half light', 'The book appears to be erotica. But without actual erotica.', '0', '0'),
(613, 614, '0x0100003400003F88', 'PLAZA ORB / boiadeiroculture', 'The book says you must attain a *Franconigerian hardbody*. At the nearest gym.', '0', '0'),
(614, 615, '0x0100003400003F96', 'PLAZA ORB / book jankaus', 'It takes willpower to even read the author\'s name: Jan Kaus. From Igaunia.', '0', '0'),
(615, 616, '0x0100003400003F9F', 'PLAZA ORB / loos radio city', 'You memorize the title: Loos, \'87: Radio City. Seems important.', '0', '0'),
(616, 617, '0x0100003600003A41', 'PLAZA / THE GARDENER', 'The Gardener stands on the corner of Whirling and is there to help you navigate the streets of Martinaise. Later it turns out she\'s a Union spy. You get to know from here that Joyce is in town.', '396', '69'),
(617, 618, '0x01000037000000E3', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / kim in your room', 'Kim tries not to look at your broken down bathroom door.', '0', '0'),
(618, 619, '0x0100004000002A83', 'CONTAINERYARD / LEO new barks', 'Replacement barks for Leo to test out.', '79', '0'),
(619, 620, '0x0100004000002C17', 'WHIRLING / SLEEPER barks', 'Zzzzzzz...', '0', '0'),
(620, 621, '0x01000042000004D5', 'COAST ORB / boardwalkexplainer', 'Nothing on the boardwalk suggests the sniper shot came from here. Maybe something will turn up later?', '0', '0'),
(621, 622, '0x01000042000004DB', 'COAST ORB / boardwalkagainexp', 'No trace of the hanged man\'s shooting *on* the boardwalk -- maybe look *under* it again?', '0', '0'),
(622, 623, '0x0100004500000F65', 'Who put the clothes in the trash?', 'The victim\'s clothes were in the trash container out back, neatly folded. Who could have put them there, and why? Only the Whirling staff was supposed to have the key.', '0', '0'),
(623, 624, '0x0100004500001225', 'Style your paperwork', 'You and your Conceptualization skill have decided to style that paperwork so it\'d be cooler somehow. Be on the lookout, but know -- this will take *time*.', '0', '0'),
(624, 625, '0x01000045000012EB', 'INVENTORY / LEDGER OF FAILURE', 'Perform a closer inspection of the ledger found in the trash (your official paperwork). Find:\n1. serial number\n2. forms\n3. notes on cases\n4. wife\'s letter\n5. toilet smell', '396', '216'),
(625, 626, '0x0100004500002441', 'Read your ledger and name the case', 'This case needs an official name. Go to your INVENTORY, and INTERACT with the Damaged Ledger to give it one. (Finding the right line may take some time.)', '0', '0'),
(626, 627, '0x010000450000536A', 'YARD / HANGED MAN BULLET', 'This is the final phase of the hanged man:\n1. White check to find bullet\n2. Failure to find fridge\n3. Bagging him and taking it away', '396', '389'),
(627, 628, '0x0100004500005904', 'Wash off the death smell', 'You reek of death. Wash it off. There\'s a bathtub in your room in the Whirling-in-Rags. A good place to visit once you can have some privacy.', '0', '0'),
(628, 629, '0x0100004500005B43', 'DOOMED / MOODBOARD', 'Fortress Accident\'s whiteboard. Has three sections: game-related concept art, production schedule and Soona\'s notes.', '252', '0'),
(629, 630, '0x0100004500005B49', 'DOOMED / RADIOCOMPUTER', 'RADIOCOMPUTER -- WIRRAL UNTETHERED! HEAT DEATH!', '396', '256'),
(630, 631, '0x0100004500005EB4', 'PIER / JOYCE INTRO', 'Joyce is on her boat. She welcomes you and tells you about the situation, her role in it, what happened w hanged man.\n1. Finishes task: find wild pines rep\n2. Finishes task: reality lowdown\n2. Gives task: investigate traffic jam\n3. Volition white to get 130 real', '396', '380'),
(631, 632, '0x0100004500005EDE', 'PIER / JOYCE LYNCHING AND TATTOOS', 'The lynching hub\nThe tattoos hub', '396', '380'),
(632, 633, '0x0100004500007847', 'Joyce\'s info on the lynching', 'There is something she wants to tell you -- you just have to present her with your badge to hear it. *Or* perhaps if you did her a favour she could wave off the formality? Whatever the case, you need to know what she knows.', '0', '0'),
(633, 634, '0x0100004500008AA7', 'The victim\'s tattoos', 'You have a photo of the hanged man\'s tattoos. Maybe someone can decipher them, tell you what they mean? You should probably talk to about two people about them for this.', '0', '0'),
(634, 635, '0x0100004500008EDC', 'PIER / JOYCE ON EVRART', 'EVRART HUB and all such relevant information. Also tells you Discovery of Insulinde story.', '396', '380'),
(635, 636, '0x0100004500008EEE', 'PIER / JOYCE REALITY HUB', 'Reality hub', '396', '380'),
(636, 637, '0x010000450000B72A', 'JOYCE / REALITY TIMES', 'Times part of hub, solves TASK.reality lowdown', '380', '0'),
(637, 638, '0x010000450000E005', 'Get Joyce to tell you about discovery of Insulinde', 'Joyce has said she will tell you about the discovery of the Insulindian isola, one day. You have a feeling you need to tell her things in return -- things you do for Evrart, maybe?', '0', '0'),
(638, 639, '0x010000450000E551', 'WHIRLING F1 / THE GARDENER MAIN', 'The Gardener turns out to be a Union fixer. Slightly different model and portrait. Short *smug* dialogue directing you to Hardie, referencing last dialogue.', '396', '395'),
(639, 640, '0x010000450000E564', 'WHIRLING F1 / HARDIE', 'Titus Hardie, leader of the militant union wing Hardie Boys. Mass dialogue + Gardener and Boys:\n\n1) Admit they lynched the man because of a rape.\n2) WHITE: Rhetoric to get them to tell you Klaasje was victim (Evrart makes easier -- leads to Klaasje, Klaasje betrays)\n3) React to Klaasje\'s betrayal\n4) WHITE: Suggestion to get them to counterbetray and reveal Assassination\n5) something to get them to reveal Instigator (Ruby)', '396', '103'),
(640, 641, '0x010000450000E5F3', 'WHIRLING F1 / HORSE FACED WOMAN', 'Horse-Faced-Woman (Minot)', '396', '395');
INSERT INTO `conversations` (`index`, `conversationId`, `articyId`, `title`, `description`, `actorId`, `conversantId`) VALUES
(641, 642, '0x010000450000E622', 'WHIRLING F1 / MAN WITH SUNGLASSES', 'Man with Sunglasses (Vicquemare)', '396', '92'),
(642, 643, '0x010000450000E66D', 'WHIRLING F1 ORB / hidden door', 'There\'s a door there, partially obscured by posters.', '0', '0'),
(643, 644, '0x010000450000E67A', 'WHIRLING F1 ORB / door conclusion', 'Could it lead to the same room as the kitchen door?', '0', '0'),
(644, 645, '0x010000450000E690', 'WHIRLING F1 / INDUSTRIAL STOVE', 'You can use the stove to boil the hanged man\'s boots when Kim is not around.', '396', '395'),
(645, 646, '0x010000450000E699', 'WHIRLING F1 ORB / door been there', 'It used to lead to the pinball repair shop.', '0', '0'),
(646, 647, '0x010000450000E6DA', 'WHIRLING F1 / SPARE WORKSHOP KEYS', 'Somewhere in the room are the previous owner\'s spare keys to the pinball workshop (door in kitchen). This is the (perc check hidden) dialogue where you find them. (One path to hidden access to roof)1) Mis-connect to instigator because of room', '396', '294'),
(647, 648, '0x010000450000E6F5', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / bills on desk', 'Hotel bill calculations. Looks like she\'s had an extended stay.', '0', '0'),
(648, 649, '0x010000450000E6FC', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / dirty clothes', 'Piles of dirty clothes; a woman\'s.', '0', '0'),
(649, 650, '0x010000450000E703', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / sad feeling', 'This room has *Sad* all over it -- reminds you of your own', '0', '0'),
(650, 651, '0x010000450000E70A', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / three months of bills', 'She\'s made around four months of payments for this room.', '0', '0'),
(651, 652, '0x010000450000E718', 'WHIRLING F3 / CLEAR WINDOW VISCAL DIFFICULT', 'This window has been recently replaced. High perception to notice. This dialogue gets a viscal and becomes trivial once someone admits Assassination', '396', '288'),
(652, 653, '0x010000450000E722', 'WHIRLING ROOF ORB / astra menthol', 'The smell of cigarette smoke in the air: *Astra* Menthol.', '0', '0'),
(653, 654, '0x010000450000E729', 'WHIRLING F3 / BARRED DOOR', 'This is the door on the roof. \nPhys Inst white get in', '396', '290'),
(654, 655, '0x010000450000E738', 'WHIRLING ROOF ORB / wildflowers', 'Look! A handful of dried white wildflowers...', '0', '0'),
(655, 656, '0x010000450000E73F', 'WHIRLING ROOF ORB / handeye catch', 'hand eye coordination bubble to catch the wildflowers', '396', '415'),
(656, 657, '0x010000450000E763', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / bed', 'The bed has been hastily made.', '0', '0'),
(657, 658, '0x010000450000E78D', 'WHIRLING F1 / ELEVATOR', '1. You experience the lovely elevator and wonder what it was used for.\n2. You can go up and down.', '0', '0'),
(658, 659, '0x010000450000E795', 'WHIRLING F1 ORB / franconigerian conquest pinballer', 'This pinball says \'Franconigerian\'. The theme is horses and swords.', '0', '0'),
(659, 660, '0x010000450000E79C', 'WHIRLING F1 ORB / mysterious woman pinballer', 'This pinball is \'White Deora\'. The backglass shows a female figure in mourning.', '0', '0'),
(660, 661, '0x010000450000E7AD', 'WHIRLING F1 ORB / play pinball', '1. Let\'s play pinball.\n2. Kim \"Pinball\" Kitsuragi back story.', '0', '0'),
(661, 662, '0x010000450000E7C1', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / tools', 'Boxes of tools and replacement parts line the shelves.', '0', '0'),
(662, 663, '0x010000450000E7C8', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / peephole shivers', '1. Doomed felt.\n2. This is not just a hole -- this is a peephole.', '0', '0'),
(663, 664, '0x010000450000E7CF', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / small perforation', 'There\'s a tiny hole in the wall. You see a bedroom on the other side.', '0', '0'),
(664, 665, '0x010000450000E7DC', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / pinball workshop', '1. This was a pinball workshop.\n2. Was the Whirling-in-Rags part of the doomed commercial area task gained.', '0', '0'),
(665, 666, '0x010000450000E7EB', 'WHIRLING F3 / FOOTPRINTS IN THE DUST', '1. See tracks from what seem to be boots.\n2. Reveals not odd-soled if you return after suspecting Ruby. (Anti-red-herring.)', '0', '0'),
(666, 667, '0x010000450000E817', 'Send victim\'s body to processing', 'Once you\'re done with it, send the corpse to Processing (Lieutenant Kitsuragi will take care of it). Check twice to see whether you\'re done with all corpse-related tasks -- after you\'ve sent the body away, you can\'t take it back.', '0', '0'),
(667, 668, '0x010000450000E835', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / body down', 'In the yard below a corpse lies under the pine tree.', '0', '0'),
(668, 669, '0x010000450000E83C', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / body up', 'In the yard below a corpse hangs from the pine tree.', '0', '0'),
(669, 670, '0x010000450000E843', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / body gone', 'You see the yard below. The corpse is no longer there.', '0', '0'),
(670, 671, '0x010000450000E871', 'Find speed and sniff it', 'The hangover is coming on *mega* strong now. You need more speed in your bloodstream. Find some, put it in your hand (equip it in the HELD slot in your INVENTORY), and off we go!', '0', '0'),
(671, 672, '0x010000450000EAF0', 'WHIRLING F3 / CLEAR WINDOW VISCAL TRIVIAL', 'The trivial version of the window -- for when you know about Assassination', '0', '0'),
(672, 673, '0x010000450000EBFE', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / watching you', 'You feel someone watching you, behind the glass door -- a woman.', '0', '0'),
(673, 674, '0x010000450000EC22', 'WHIRLING ROOF ORB / wind picks them up', '...the wind brushes them off the roof. They\'re gone.', '0', '0'),
(674, 675, '0x010000450000ED13', 'WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE RAPE VOLITION', '3) What happened? (rape)\n4) Volition white (manipulating you)', '382', '395'),
(675, 676, '0x010000450000ED53', 'WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE TAPE LELY', '5) heard tape / gonna hear tape\n6) Lely details', '382', '395'),
(676, 677, '0x010000450000EDC3', 'Who made the call reporting the crime?', 'Someone reported the hanging to the RCM. Maybe if you find out who it was, it may shed new light on the events. You have an idea where to start, but the caller could have been anyone.', '0', '0'),
(677, 678, '0x010000450000EDD0', 'Ask Klaasje about Sunday night', 'When Kim\'s not around to stop you, ask Klaasje about what she heard from her room the night before you emerged into Reality. She must know something.', '0', '0'),
(678, 679, '0x010000450000EE57', 'Explore the Whirling’s secret passages', 'There are strange doors in the Whirling. No one knows where they lead. Find a way in and see what\'s hidden there, in the hostel cafeteria\'s forgotten corners.', '0', '0'),
(679, 680, '0x010000450000F04E', 'KIM SWITCH / KLAASJE REACTION', 'Kim reacts to you losing your shit (Composure fail) when the Hardie boys said the victim is a young woman called Klaasje in the Whirling-in-Rags.', '395', '0'),
(680, 681, '0x010000450000F453', 'WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE barks', 'KOSMOS! INCLUDES VO!', '0', '0'),
(681, 682, '0x010000450000F6A7', 'Sing karaoke', 'You need to find a sufficiently tragic tape, then play it on a boombox to memorize the lyrics. Then ask the cafeteria manager to perform. (Preferably in the evening. More people at the bar then.)', '0', '0'),
(682, 683, '0x0100004500010D5A', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / narcomania afterthought', 'narcomania afterthought', '406', '0'),
(683, 684, '0x0100004500011649', 'INVENTORY / DRIED MAY BELLS', 'This dialogue is attached to the \"dried_may_bells\" item.', '396', '0'),
(684, 685, '0x010000450001273A', 'KIM SWITCH / DISCUSSING KLAASJE DOWNSTAIRS', 'this should blink ONLY DOWNSTAIRS and after Klaasje rape hub exit', '395', '0'),
(685, 686, '0x01000045000128ED', 'INVENTORY / LELY TAPE', 'tape now interactable in inventory, if you have the boombox. Lely-Kortenaer banter for interrogate Klaasje sequence', '0', '0'),
(686, 687, '0x0100004500012C9C', 'Doorgunner Megamix', 'Hardie gave you a recording where the hanged man supposedly testifies to his intent to rape and pillage. Have a listen on a playback device -- either in your room; or find one from a pawnshop.', '0', '0'),
(687, 688, '0x0100004500012D6C', 'WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE FULL STORY', '6) hardie confessed, whole story (ruby leader)\n7) drama white (ruby suspect)', '382', '395'),
(688, 689, '0x01000045000132B1', 'Question Klaasje about the dead man', 'Klaasje told you she can\'t talk about him now, but you need *specifics* -- height, build, etc, to confirm your autopsy. Ask a little later, when she has collected herself.', '0', '0'),
(689, 690, '0x0100004500013866', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / age afterthought', 'how old are you afterthought', '402', '0'),
(690, 691, '0x010000450001603B', 'WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE END', '11) Shivers white', '382', '395'),
(691, 692, '0x0100004500017386', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / love did him in', 'did in by love afterthought', '404', '0'),
(692, 693, '0x0100004500017511', 'Make Titus give up Ruby\'s location', 'Ruby was the organizer of the hanging. She\'s also *missing*, but the Hardie boys will be tight-lipped about her location. You need to get them to open up. Have you *fully* explored the Whirling? Analysed the site of the murder? Truly and *thoroughly* interrogated Klaasje? All this might make convincing them easier.', '0', '0'),
(693, 694, '0x0100004500017A03', 'Inspect Klaasje\'s buoy', 'There\'s a buoy West of the boardwalk on the coast, somewhere in the reeds. It has Miss Oranje\'s fake documents in it...', '0', '0'),
(694, 695, '0x0100004500019480', 'LANDS END ORB / cigarette butts', 'Cigarette butts, cleaned away under a rock: brand Tioumoutiri.', '0', '0'),
(695, 696, '0x0100004500019487', 'LANDS END ORB / rickety ladder', 'This ladder is too rusty to climb. The sea air has eaten away at it.', '0', '0'),
(696, 697, '0x010000450001948E', 'LANDS END ORB / campfire remains', 'Someone\'s made a campfire here, a long time ago.', '0', '0'),
(697, 698, '0x0100004500019495', 'LANDS END ORB / lands end shot viscal', 'the conclusion dialogue where you conclude the shot did not come from land\'s end. this fires only if you have  TASK.check_lands_end', '0', '0'),
(698, 699, '0x0100004500019690', 'Arrest Klaasje', 'There is a hidden way to arrest Klaasje and have Kim take her to Precinct 57 for safe keeping. She is not to be trusted.', '0', '0'),
(699, 700, '0x0100004500019797', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / red thread inside', 'A red thread. Made of nylon. It leads out of the room and onto the roof...', '0', '0'),
(700, 701, '0x010000450001979E', 'WHIRLING ROOF ORB / red thread outside if did not click on thread inside', 'Red thread. Made of nylon. It leads into the room...', '0', '0'),
(701, 702, '0x01000045000197A5', 'WHIRLING ROOF ORB / red thread outside if clicked on thread inside', 'The thread is tied to the antenna.', '0', '0'),
(702, 703, '0x01000045000197AC', 'WHIRLING F3 ORB / red thread inside if clicked on thread outside', 'The thread is tied to a bookcase on the wall.', '0', '0'),
(703, 704, '0x0100004500019C4E', 'WHIRLING F2 / KIM WAKEUP', 'If you succeeded the final Authority check to warn Kim.', '395', '0'),
(704, 705, '0x0100004500019C5F', 'WHIRLING F2 / CUNO WAKEUP', 'If you didn\'t make the authority check.', '5', '0'),
(705, 706, '0x0100004500019CA5', 'Find solution to strike deadlock', 'There is a secret way to solve the deadlock. It\'s not easy, includes a lot of back and forth between the two sides, but it\'s possible. Everything is always possible.', '0', '0'),
(706, 707, '0x010000450001A725', 'Are you La Puta Madre\'s peone?', 'Ruby said you were a notoriously corrupt cop. La Puta Madre\'s peone. That\'s why she was scared of you. When you get the chance, call your station to find out more -- *if* you dare.', '0', '0'),
(707, 708, '0x010000450001A9C5', 'WHIRLING F2 ORB / fixed window', 'Newly replaced glass, shining in the morning light.', '0', '0'),
